- model: blawx.ruledoc
  pk: 2
  fields:
    ruledoc_name: art20 GDPR
    rule_text: "Right to data portability\r\n\r\n1. The data subject shall have the
      right to receive the personal data concerning him or her, which he or she has
      provided to a controller, in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable
      format and have the right to transmit those data to another controller without
      hindrance from the controller to which the personal data have been provided,
      where:\r\n  (a) the processing is based on consent pursuant to point (a) of
      Article 6(1) or point (a) of Article 9(2) or on a contract pursuant to point
      (b) of Article 6(1); and\r\n  (b) the processing is carried out by automated
      means.\r\n2. In exercising his or her right to data portability pursuant to
      paragraph 1, the data subject shall have the right to have the personal data
      transmitted directly from one controller to another, where technically feasible.\r\n3.
      The exercise of the right referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article shall be
      without prejudice to Article 17. That right shall not apply to processing necessary
      for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise
      of official authority vested in the controller."
    rule_slug: art20-gdpr
    akoma_ntoso: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><akomaNtoso xmlns="http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0"><act><preface><p
      class="title"><shortTitle>Right to data portability</shortTitle></p></preface><body><section
      eId="sec_1"><num>1</num><intro><p>The data subject shall have the right to receive
      the personal data concerning him or her, which he or she has provided to a controller,
      in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format and have the right
      to transmit those data to another controller without hindrance from the controller
      to which the personal data have been provided, where:</p></intro><paragraph
      eId="sec_1__para_a"><num>a</num><content><p>the processing is based on consent
      pursuant to point (a) of Article 6(1) or point (a) of Article 9(2) or on a contract
      pursuant to point (b) of Article 6(1); and</p></content></paragraph><paragraph
      eId="sec_1__para_b"><num>b</num><content><p>the processing is carried out by
      automated means.</p></content></paragraph></section><section eId="sec_2"><num>2</num><content><p>In
      exercising his or her right to data portability pursuant to paragraph 1, the
      data subject shall have the right to have the personal data transmitted directly
      from one controller to another, where technically feasible.</p></content></section><section
      eId="sec_3"><num>3</num><content><p>The exercise of the right referred to in
      paragraph 1 of this Article shall be without prejudice to Article 17. That right
      shall not apply to processing necessary for the performance of a task carried
      out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in
      the controller.</p></content></section></body></act></akomaNtoso>
